# /commit-message

Generate a **Conventional Commit message for an iOS (Swift) project** using the
current staged git changes and branch name. The commit message should follow
best practices and include the Jira issue ID when available.

---

## Instructions

When this command is triggered:

### 1. Inspect Git Context

Run the following commands to understand the change.

```bash
git branch --show-current
```

```bash
git diff --staged --stat
```

```bash
git diff --staged
```

```bash
git log --oneline -10
```

Use these to determine:

- What files changed
- What part of the app is affected
- Existing commit message style

---

### 2. Detect Jira Issue ID

Extract Jira ID from the branch name using the pattern:

```
[A-Z]+-[0-9]+
```

Example branch names:

```
feat/IOS-19839-course-player
fix/IOS-19838-webview-crash
tasl/IOS-19830-video-player-fix
```

Detected IDs:

```
IOS-19839
IOS-19838
IOS-19830
```

If none is found, ask the user for the Jira ID.

---

### 3. Determine Commit Type

Choose the correct Conventional Commit type.

| Type | When to use |
|-----|-------------|
| feat | New feature |
| fix | Bug fix |
| perf | Performance improvement |
| refactor | Code restructuring |
| docs | Documentation |
| style | Formatting only |
| test | Tests only |
| chore | Maintenance tasks |
| build | Build or dependency changes |
| ci | CI/CD changes |

---

### 4. Determine Scope (iOS)

Infer the scope from changed files.

Common scopes for iOS projects:

| Scope | Area |
|------|------|
| ui | SwiftUI / UIKit UI |
| webview | WKWebView logic |
| network | API layer |
| auth | Authentication |
| analytics | Event tracking |
| player | Video / media player |
| storage | CoreData / persistence |
| course | LMS / course logic |
| build | Xcode build settings |

Example:

```
fix(webview)
feat(ui)
refactor(network)
```

---

### 5. Generate the Commit Message

Use this format:

```
type(scope): short description

Optional longer explanation describing what and why.

Jira: ISSUE-ID
```

Rules:

- Subject line ≤ 72 characters
- Use imperative mood
- Do not end subject with a period
- Wrap body text at 72 characters

---

## Example Outputs

### Bug Fix

```
fix(webview): handle iframe postMessage crash on iPhone

Adds validation before processing iframe messages coming from
course content. Prevents crash observed in WKWebView on iPhone.

Jira: LMS-341
```

---

### Feature

```
feat(ui): implement adaptive dashboard card layout

Adds layout logic to support dynamic card counts from 1 to 5.
Cards resize and adjust rows automatically.

Jira: APP-512
```

---

### Refactor

```
refactor(network): simplify API error handling

Centralizes response error parsing inside NetworkManager and
removes duplicated logic across service layers.

Jira: APP-402
```

---

### Build Update

```
chore(build): update iOS deployment target to 16.0
```

---

## Additional Guidelines

Avoid vague commit messages:

❌

```
fix bug
update code
changes
```

Prefer descriptive messages:

✅

```
fix(webview): prevent crash when iframe sends empty message
```

---

## Output

Return **only the generated commit message**, ready to paste into:

```
git commit -m "<message>"
```
